    "enText": "<p>Ali wakes up early in the morning feeling unwell. He has a headache and a sore throat, and he feels tired. His mother decides that he should visit a doctor. After breakfast, they get ready and leave the house together. They go to a local health center near their home.</p><p>When they arrive, Ali and his mother sit in the waiting room. There are other patients waiting quietly. Some people are reading, and some are using their phones. Ali feels a little nervous because he does not like hospitals, but his mother tells him not to worry. After a short time, the nurse calls Ali’s name.</p><p>Ali goes into the doctor’s room with his mother. The doctor greets them kindly and asks Ali how he feels. Ali explains that he has a headache, a sore throat, and feels weak. The doctor listens carefully and asks a few more questions. She asks when the pain started and if Ali has a fever.</p><p>The doctor checks Ali’s temperature and listens to his breathing. She looks at his throat and ears. Ali tries to stay calm and follows the doctor’s instructions. The doctor tells Ali that he has a simple cold and does not need to worry. She explains that many students get sick during the school year.</p><p>The doctor writes a prescription and gives some advice. She tells Ali to rest at home, drink plenty of water, and eat light food. She also gives him medicine for his headache and throat. The doctor says Ali should stay at home for a few days and avoid cold drinks.</p><p>After the visit, Ali and his mother go to the pharmacy. The pharmacist gives them the medicine and explains how to use it. Ali listens carefully because he wants to get better quickly. When they return home, Ali feels relieved. He understands that visiting a doctor is important when you feel sick.</p><p>At home, Ali rests in his bed and follows the doctor’s advice. He drinks warm tea and sleeps. He feels thankful that the doctor helped him and explains everything clearly. For Ali, visiting a doctor is not scary anymore because he knows it helps him stay healthy.</p>",
