    "title": "B1 A Difficult Choice",
    "enText": "<p>Laura had always believed that life was about making the right decisions. She was careful, organized, and planned everything in advance. After finishing high school, she moved to another city for university. Living alone was difficult at first, but Laura learned how to manage her time, money, and responsibilities.</p><p>Laura studied engineering, a subject that required discipline and patience. She spent long hours studying and working on projects. Sometimes she felt tired, but she was proud of herself. Her family supported her and believed she had a bright future. Everything seemed to be going well until Laura faced a difficult choice in her third year.</p><p>One day, Laura received an email from a company offering her a full-time job. The position was well-paid and respected. Many students dreamed of such an opportunity. At the same time, Laura also received an acceptance letter for a student exchange program abroad. This program would allow her to study in another country for one year.</p><p>Laura felt confused. The job offered financial security and experience, while the exchange program offered adventure, learning, and personal growth. She talked to her family and friends. Some said she should take the job because opportunities like this do not come often. Others encouraged her to go abroad and explore the world while she was young.</p><p>For weeks, Laura could not decide. She made lists of advantages and disadvantages. She imagined different futures. At night, she felt anxious and unsure. She realized that there was no perfect choice, only different paths.</p><p>In the end, Laura chose the exchange program. She knew the decision was risky, but she felt it was right for her. Living in another country was challenging. She struggled with the language and missed her family. However, she also met new people, learned new ways of thinking, and became more independent.</p><p>When Laura returned home, she was not the same person. She was more confident and open-minded. Finding a job took time, but she did not regret her choice. She learned that difficult decisions help people grow.</p><p>Laura understood that life does not follow one straight line. Sometimes, choosing uncertainty leads to the most valuable experiences.</p>",
    "trText": "<p>Laura hayatın doğru kararlar vermekle ilgili olduğuna inanırdı. Dikkatli, planlı ve düzenliydi. Liseyi bitirdikten sonra üniversite için başka bir şehre taşındı. İlk başta yalnız yaşamak zordu ama zamanla her şeyi yönetmeyi öğrendi.</p><p>Laura mühendislik okuyordu. Dersleri zordu ama kendisiyle gurur duyuyordu. Ailesi onu destekliyordu. Üçüncü sınıfta zor bir seçimle karşılaştı. İyi maaşlı bir iş teklifi aldı. Aynı zamanda yurt dışı öğrenci değişim programına kabul edildi.</p><p>İki seçenek arasında kaldı. İş güvenliydi, yurt dışı ise keşifti. Günlerce düşündü. Sonunda yurt dışına gitmeyi seçti. Zorlandı ama çok şey öğrendi. Daha güçlü bir insan oldu.</p><p>Döndüğünde iş bulmak zaman aldı ama pişman olmadı. Hayatın tek bir yolu olmadığını anladı.</p>",
